The paper discusses the transmission strategy of cognitive users in IEEE 802.11 based networks, which falls under the category of networked and internet-based systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm is based on reinforcement learning (cs.AI) and involves decision-making and optimization (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the constraint of message passing and the use of backoff counters, which are related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the simulation results are compared with contemporary solutions, which involves machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
